
// The code constructs an HTML string using the [strings.builder] slot. It appends a header tag with "Hello ", then appends the value of the [name] argument, and finally appends a paragraph thanking the user for joining. The [strings.builder.append] slot is used to sequentially build the HTML content.
strings.builder
   strings.builder.append:"<h1>Hello "
   strings.builder.append:x:@.arguments/*/name
   strings.builder.append:</h1><p>Thanks for joining us.</p>
